# 4. Get All Files

### Method

```http
GET
```

### URL

```text
http://localhost:5000/api/files
```

### Body

No body required.

### Expected Response

```json
[
    {
        "_id": "...",
        "storageType": "local"
    },
    {
        "_id": "...",
        "storageType": "cloudinary"
    }
]
```

---

# 5. Get Single File

### Method

```http
GET
```

### URL

```text
http://localhost:5000/api/files/:id
```

Example

```text
http://localhost:5000/api/files/6843f3b5f1a45d4ab1234567
```

### Expected Response

```json
{
    "_id": "...",
    "originalName": "image.jpg",
    "storageType": "local"
}
```

---

# 6. Display Image Stored in MongoDB

### Method

```http
GET
```

### URL

```text
http://localhost:5000/api/image/:id
```

Example

```text
http://localhost:5000/api/image/6843f3b5f1a45d4ab1234567
```

### Expected Result

The browser/Postman will display the image stored inside MongoDB.

---

# 7. Delete File

### Method

```http
DELETE
```

### URL

```text
http://localhost:5000/api/files/:id
```

Example

```text
http://localhost:5000/api/files/6843f3b5f1a45d4ab1234567
```

### Expected Response

```json
{
    "message": "Deleted Successfully"
}
```

